{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"60accbdf-3b0a-4e3e-9667-16f5ada05192","content":"Here's a quick overview of common web API templates and their auth options:\n\n### .NET (`dotnet new`)\n- **Template:** `webapi` or `webapicontrollers`\n- **Auth options (`--auth`):** `None`, `IndividualB2C`, `SingleOrg`, `Windows`\n\n### Node.js / Express\n- **Template:** `express-generator` or manual setup\n- **Auth:** Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, Local), express-jwt, Auth0 SDK\n\n### Python / FastAPI\n- **Template:** `fastapi` project scaffold\n- **Auth:** OAuth2 with JWT (built-in support), python-jose, Authlib\n\n### ASP.NET Core (most structured)\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C   # Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg       # Azure AD (single tenant)\n```\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"74836bd8-75e2-4ff6-afb7-6edf94402766","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular frameworks.","outputTokens":291,"requestId":"403E:2E9247:D8EB529:F21DBB3:69EC0DEF"},"id":"904eba16-1c9e-4bb7-a084-8c60f1bf2ffd","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:31.481Z","parentId":"9e8af4b5-cdd0-485b-98a2-3fdfedda3429"}
